						               													<description>In Patou'che!, each player embodies a shepherd who dreams of having the largest flock of sheep. But watch out for the prowling wolf, he also likes sheep, but to eat them! In order to protect their sheep, players can count on their faithful sheepdogs: the Patous. A cooperative mode also allows everyone to play together against the wolf.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;On a player&amp;rsquo;s turn, they can roll the dice up to 3 times, keeping at least 1 die after each roll. The wolf side causes the wolf to move, the sheep side wins a sheep, and the sheepdog side wins a patou. Once the result of the dice suits the player, or after a maximum of 3 throws, the action of each die is applied.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;As soon as a player has 6 Sheep cards, each of the other players plays one last time. The player with the most Sheep on all his cards is declared the winner. In case of a tie, the player with the fewest Sheepdog cards wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
